This button text seems to long to me:

comment.body:
Our buttons seems grey instead of white, like buttons comings from Leaflet/plugins:

![image](https://github.com/umap-project/umap/assets/146023/1a4ac084-ed44-420e-8099-bafef4f3c19b)

I'd say we should keep them white, or make them all grey.

commits.message: Prevent more useless redraw when editing global settings

pull_request.title: Round range step to 1 digit
pull_request.body:
Before:
![Screenshot from 2023-10-26 22-37-56](https://github.com/umap-project/umap/assets/146023/0c409557-1b99-404b-b084-373cb0ee8c0e)

After:
![Screenshot from 2023-10-26 22-37-15](https://github.com/umap-project/umap/assets/146023/ae8bdbba-3735-4582-870f-05c41bf7232f)

I don't think we really have cases where we'd need 2 digits rounding.

commits.message:
Merge pull request #1380 from umap-project/range-step-rounding

Round range step to 1 digit

Increase maxZoomLimit to 24

Even if this limit is not a hard limit, just a warning, we now
have been proven some maps using custom backgrounds use zooms
greater than 20.

Eg. this maps which allows zoom until 23:

https://umap.openstreetmap.fr/fr/map/cimetiere-asnieres-la-giraud_716488

Merge pull request #1381 from umap-project/max-zoom-limit-24

Increase maxZoomLimit to 24
